    CoreCollectors
    A factory of Collectors that allows to collect the stream of values into linked or sorted sets and the stream of entries and any other types into the linked or the sorted map.
    CoreStreamUtils
    Utility-class that provides methods to transform the stream or var-args-arrays of values into linked or sorted sets and stream or var-args-arrays of entries into linked or sorted map.

    DumpUtils
    Utility-class that is a static facade of ObjectPrinter.ToString, where the serializing of an object is provided with JacksonTree.
    Highlight
    This class represents an immutable multidimensional Map of highlight rules, where the value of rule is either Ansi-Style or HTML-Style (mostly the color of text).
    Highlight.Kind
    The kind of JSON or YAML tokens to highlight
    Highlight.Place
    This record represents a key in multidimensional Map to store and lookup the highlight-rules.
    Highlight.Rule
    Individual highlight-rule - the correspondence between place and style to apply.
    Highlight.Structure
    The target logical structure of rendered document (JSON or YAML)
    Highlight.Target
    The target format of output (HTML-document/HTML-fragment, console with ANSI-escape sequences, ...)
    JacksonTree
    A static-factory that provides an implementation of of TreeDumper.Node over JsonNode, which is the base data-unit that is provided by Jackson-library.
    JacksonUtils
    Utility class to serialize / de-serialize JSON-Objects and JSON-Arrays using Jackson Library

    JacksonUtils.JsonError
     
    JarFileInfo
     
    JsonHtmlDumper
    Implementation of TreeDumper that dumps into the passed PrintStream the tree of a JSON logical structure in HTML-Style target format (HTML-CSS is coming soon).
    JsonSvgDumper
    Implementation of TreeDumper that dumps into the passed PrintStream the tree of a JSON logical structure in SVG-Attrs target format (SVG-Class is coming soon).
    JsonTxtDumper
    Implementation of TreeDumper that dumps into the passed PrintStream the tree of a JSON logical structure in ANSI-Txt target format.
    MergeFunction
    This enumeration is used to handle the entries with the same key, when the stream of entries are collected into linked map or sorted map.
    ObjectPrinter
    Interface to represent any Java-Object in most popular hierarchical structures (JSON and YAML) and with suitable output formats (TXT, HTML, SVG) with a flexible way to control the highlighting of elements.
    ObjectPrinter.StdOut
     
    ObjectPrinter.ToFile
     
    ObjectPrinter.ToString
     
    ObjectPrinter.UnitOp
    This Java-record is a kind of element in multidimensional virtual methods' table, which acts as a bridge between two hierarchies of different implementations of: TreeDumper.Node (the default factory is JacksonTree.DEFAULT_JACKSON_TREE) ObjectPrinter - StdOut, ToString and ToFile Further interaction two hierarchies are performed via well known and very popular Visitor pattern
    OuterTagUtils
    Utility-class to wrap inner-HTML or inner-SVG with outer HTML-tags
    PrintUtils
    Utility-class that is a static facade of ObjectPrinter.DEFAULT_STD_OUT, where the serializing of an object is provided with JacksonTree.
    PropertiesUtils
    Utility-class that simplifies the access to environment-variables, Java system-properties and the content of any other properties-files at file-system or in classpath.

    This interface represents the ability to dump the data of JSON-like and YAML-like hierarchical structure in multicolor TEXT-base, HTML-base and SVG-base formats.
